news.title: Over 500 applications received by Pune development body for regularisation
news.para: The official said that the development charges for land is 0.5 % of land charges and 2% of built-up area as per the ready reckoned rates. The rates for these 566 structures were assessed and given permission for regularisation.

news.title: Chhattisgarh amends rules to simplify regularization of unauthorized development
news.para: Applications for the area under the urban local bodies have to be submitted in the municipal corporation and municipalities concerned while applications outside the purview of the municipal corporation and municipality but under the planning area will have to be submitted in the town and country planning office.

news.title: Andhra Pradesh shifts its gaze to energy savings in building sector
news.para: This sector contributes to about 33% of the total electricity consumption, becoming the second largest consumer. The commercial buildings in Andhra Pradesh draw around 3,000 million units (MU) per annum.

news.title: No bricks to be sold in Ludhiana till September 17
news.para: The development might lead to crisis for the construction industry and also impact ongoing residential and commercial construction projects in the city.

news.title: Thiruvananthapuram corporation invites EoI to prepare DPR for mini township plan
news.para: The city corporation has invited expression of interest (EoI) from registered structural consultancy firms or consultants to prepare a detailed project report (DPR), including structural design of a multistoreyed building proposed at the mini township.

news.title: GIS mapping, drones to keep tabs on illegal constructions in Pune
news.para: A pilot was launched in April-May this year which helped identify over 100 constructions. The PMRDA has procured two drones and plans to use them to keep a check on illegal constructions, said officials.

news.title: Chandigarh housing board to survey 560 small flats in Maloya today
news.para: During the door-to-door survey, 1,567 small flats were surveyed at Mauli Jagran and 4,032 at Maloya. The authority said on Monday, the rest 560 flats in Maloya will be surveyed too.

news.title: Supertech twin towers: On Day 1, eight trucks clear 180 tonnes of debris
news.para: Officials of the demolition company, Edifice Engineering, said the trucks transported the debris from Sector 93A, where the towers had once stood, to the C&D plant in Sector 80 of Noida.

news.title: Gurugram: Residents protest over hike in BPTP upkeep fee
news.para: Spread across 43 acres of land, the township was developed in multiple phases with four residential societies namely Serene, Generations, Spacio and Terra.

news.title: IGE India buys two apartments in Mumbai's Worli for Rs 151 crore
news.para: The company has purchased both the apartments spread over a total of 16,072 sq ft on the 58th and 59th floors of the project from the developer, Oberoi Realty’s subsidiary Oasis Realty, that is executing the project.

news.title: Sunteck Realty acquires 7.25 acres land in Beverly Park, Mumbai
news.para: The project is estimated to have development potential of approx 2.5 million sq ft built up area and a revenue potential of around Rs 3,000 crore.

news.title: Bengaluru: CID arrests Mantri Developers' director, son after complaints from buyers
news.para: Several homebuyers had filed complaints with Subramanyapura police stating that they were cheated of money by the builders, who had lured them with attractive offers, misleading brochures and fake schemes.

news.title: Cash-strapped Ludhiana civic body revises property tax target to Rs 130 crore
news.para: Officials claimed that they expect to recover at least Rs 60 crore by the month-end, for which they were organising special camps in commercial areas and industrial units.

news.title: Haryana: Error in property tax ID? Submit complaints via NDC
news.para: The civic body has also decided to form a separate NDC cell to immediately resolve property IDs-related grievances.

news.title: Mysuru: MUDA forms task force to control mushrooming illegal construction
news.para: The team of officials will visit the places where unauthorised construction of layouts is found. He added when it is found illegal, the layouts will be cleared by issuing them notices.
